==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perforata
<hw>Per`fo*ra"ta</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r`f⟦osl⟧*r⟦amac⟧"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See <er>Perforate</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A division of corals including
those that have a porous texture, as Porites and Madrepora; -- opposed
to <contr>Aporosa</contr>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A division of
Foraminifera, including those having perforated shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perforate</ent>⟦br⟧
